channel.description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from BUbuisnessAndMarket, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: As the last tariff-free freighters pull into LA, China trade talks will begin on Friday
item.description: Also: U.S. exports to China fall 40%, Democrats want to ban the president from owning crypto.

item.title: Americans rushing to buy cars might get stuck with high interest rates and bad loan terms
item.description: As President Donald Trump’s auto tariffs go into effect, about 20% of car loans are now for seven-year terms, according to Edmunds.

item.title: Nvidia’s CEO Jensen Huang warns of a ‘tremendous loss’ if U.S. firms lose access to China’s $50 billion AI market
item.description: “China is a very large market. It’s probably going to be a $50 billion market in the next couple or three years," Huang predicted in a TV interview.

item.title: WeightWatchers files for bankruptcy as it struggles for a place in a weight loss world dominated by Ozempic and Wegovy
item.description: Parent WW International Inc. said it has the support of nearly three-quarters of its debt holders. It expects to emerge from bankruptcy within 45 days...

item.title: It’s getting harder to tell which company is winning the AI race, Hugging Face co-founder says
item.description: Hugging Face's Thomas Wolf says that it's getting harder to tell which AI model is the best as traditional AI benchmarks become saturated.
